                     <interp inst="t17890909-80-person724" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a farrier; I know nothing but they are my mistress's property.</p>
               <p>A WITNESS sworn.</p>
               <p>Last Wednesday was week, I was coming a quarter before eight in the evening, I saw the prisoner with the bag that is here; and I had a suspicion of him; and I followed him till he got to Poor Jury-street, and there he threw it down; and I stopped him, and brought him to the Compter; and gave charge of him; and he was committed; I am sure it is the same bag; I opened the bag, and found they were horses shoes; I went to Mrs. Thrupp's in <placeName id="t17890909-80-crimeloc403">Aldermanbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17890909-80-crimeloc403" type="placeName" value="Aldermanbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17890909-80-crimeloc403" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17890909-80-off399 t17890909-80-crimeloc403"></join>, and found he worked there; and Mrs. Thrupp said, she nor any of her people could not identify them nor the iron.</p>
